%% OIDC Authorization Code flow as implemented in src/oidc_app.py
sequenceDiagram
    autonumber
    participant U as User (Browser)
    participant F as Flask app (src/oidc_app.py)
    participant O as Okta (Authorization Server)

    U->>F: GET /login
    F->>F: generate nonce, store in session
    F-->>U: 302 to Okta /authorize<br/>?client_id&redirect_uri&scope=openid+profile+email&nonce&state
    U->>O: GET /authorize
    O-->>U: login UI (with MFA)
    U->>O: submit credentials
    O-->>U: 302 to /authorization-code/callback?code=...&state=...
    U->>F: GET /authorization-code/callback?code=...
    F->>O: POST /token<br/>grant_type=authorization_code<br/>code, client_id, client_secret, redirect_uri
    O-->>F: id_token + access_token
    F->>O: GET /.well-known/jwks.json (Authlib caches)
    O-->>F: JWKS
    F->>F: verify id_token signature + iss/aud/exp/nonce
    F->>F: set session['user']
    F-->>U: 302 to /
